Latvia’s 2010 Budget Deficit Was 7.5% of GDP, TV3 Reports

-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 
2011-04-11T09:17:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/latvia-s-2010-budget-deficit-was-7-5-of-gdp-tv3-reports.html
Latvia’s budget deficit last year
was 7.5 percent of gross domestic product according to European
Union methodology, TV3’s  Neka Personiga  program reported on its
website, citing unofficial information.  The 2010 shortfall was previously estimated at 8.2 percent
of GDP, the  Baltic News Service  reported on Feb. 9. The deficit
limit for 2010, set by the country’s lenders, was 8.5 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga, Lia, at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at   wmorris@bloomberg.net  